				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 14 Dec 2019 16:05:58 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Crashington</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5028224</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">spoilers</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>They are censoring it because this is not happening for no reason. It is what happens when, in desperation, unconventional means are taken to reach ones goal. These are tests runs for the administrator, that not only failed but also went out of control.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12830530#post-4445709</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12830530/scp-4345#post-4445709</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 13 Dec 2019 18:27:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>jiim jaam</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3274225</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This article had so much to unpack it almost overwhelmed me, but I honestly came around loving it in the end. You did a great job of implying a lot of plot points without ever explicitly stating them. +1!</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Spoilers</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Spoilers</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>The use of the word &quot;imbrication,&quot; the 2 interviews, and Reynolds' scar changing places seems to suggest memories from different timelines/dimensions/universes overlapping somehow, or maybe even the displacement of entire people. But what I don't understand is why the O5s and the Administrator are making a big deal of censoring it? There's a lot of memory-swapping SCPs, why not let the Ethics Committee know about this one specifically? This isn't a criticism for the record, I'm clearly just missing something that allows me to fully understand.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12830530#post-4443193</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12830530/scp-4345#post-4443193</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 11 Dec 2019 08:24:27 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>weedfire24</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4588247</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Just to make sure I understand why the O5 and Administrator blocked this,</p> <p>is this related by any chance to <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/mackenzie-s-proposal">this 001 proposal?</a></p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>I'm saying this because anomalies from another reality coincide real well with the Administrator's secret mission and the fact that there was a complete denial for investigation by everyone clearance 6.</p> <p>As far as I understand, the individual in Interview 1 is different from the individual in Interview 2. Individual 1 has a loving wife that 2 doesn't know about, and somehow they've had their memories imprinted on each other, somehow mixing everything up.</p> <p>You have the random sword breaching containment and, unless it's a weird plug, thats somehow relevant to the article. I assume this means that it killed the containment team in another reality and injured them badly and now they've been multidimensionally imbricated with the memories.</p> <p>Then we have two instances of people accessing documents that aren't of their clearance level. The researchers, and the reader. We've been affected by this.</p> <p>I'm pretty meh on this but I'll +1</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
