					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12830530#post-4432700</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12830530/scp-4345#post-4432700</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 27 Nov 2019 03:42:40 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>A Random Day</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1841781</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>Reynolds: When I was a kid, my parents moved a lot. We'd get settled and as soon as I feel like I made a place for myself, we'd drive away. Every time it felt like leaving everything behind. Like losing everything that made me feel at home. Everything that made me feel like I was where I belong.</p> </blockquote> <p>This is still just describing an emotional event, only poorly disguised as dialogue instead of a convenient expository note. I’m still being directly spoon-fed the emotions of the characters, and to quote the a Robot Devil, “you can’t just have your characters say how they feel! That makes me feel angry!”</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
