					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12830530#post-4432496</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12830530/scp-4345#post-4432496</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 26 Nov 2019 21:08:18 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>morgenthegrey</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2037147</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'm still trying to work out exactly what's going on.</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">my&nbsp;half-baked&nbsp;guess</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>Affected people are feeling the pain of injuries they should have sustained, but didn't. (The car that sped past Reynolds actually hit him; the staff were actually injured/killed by the escaped sword.)</p> <p>I'm not clear on why the affected are experiencing the pain without the actual visible injuries. &quot;Theseus&quot; (as in &quot;ship of&quot;) makes me think that they've been or are being replaced, partially or bit by bit?</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
